HEADWORD: Uprun
<hw>Up*run"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To run up; to
ascend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The young sun⟦br⟧
That in the Ram is four degrees <qex>uprun</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[A son] of matchless might, who, like a thriving plant,⟦br⟧
<qex>Upran</qex> to manhood.</q> <rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uprush</ent>⟦br⟧
